reviews.text:
Amazing pizza!
I ordered a 20‚Äù pepperoni to go, and it was one of the best pies I‚Äôve ever had. The crust was perfect‚Äîchewy on the bottom with a super crispy outer edge. Three huge slices just about did me in. This is officially our new favorite pizza in Bismarck. The staff were friendly and helpful. I chatted with a few employees, and everyone was in a great mood‚Äîwhich is especially impressive for a crew working on Independence Day.

We ordered four slices and a calzone.
The pizza tasted exactly like it was advertised. We both lived and worked in NY for almost 20 years, and this is the first pizza place that actually reminds us of ones in the city.
The calzone was very good too.
The people working there are genuinely friendly, great environment.
The owner was very kind.
We hope nothing but success for them!

Ok, I had this a while back and really didn't like it all that much. But the problem was I got it right when they came out and thru doordash. Fast forward today I got 14 inch build your own with red sauce, pepperoni, beef and mushrooms. Not everyone's perfect combo haha, but it was great. Fantastic crust and great sauce and ingredients and way more than enough to eat. It was really good sorry I thought otherwise, great pizza thank you.

Great pizza! I haven't branched off to their other  food yet but their pizza is so solid! It is on the pricey side but that's what you can expect with a more premium pizza. Plus they have a rewards program to earn points! Both photos are a pepperoni pizza. One is 10 in and the other is their largest size. My wife says this is hands down her favorite pizza place in town! Looks like it would be a fun place to work at! Please never close!

Also the reviews talking about the crusts must be people who aren't familiar with NY style pizza. It is made differently than a puffy "fast food " pizza so I have no complaints about the crust.

Stopped by for lunch on a weekday, but had just missed their lunch specials which I found to be very reasonably priced. We had a slice of pepperoni pizza, some cheesy garlic bread, and a calzone. The bread and calzone were made hot and fresh to order, and were out to us in about 15 minutes. The slice of pizza was huge, and the thickness of the crust was perfect for folding. There is a counter with barstools lining the perimeter - it's not a place I'd hang out or select for a business meeting, but perfect for a quick lunch. The employees were friendly and efficient. My partner has been here several times for lunch and keeps going back for the lunch specials, he's also a fan of the gyro.

detailedReviews.author: Tyler Manske
detailedReviews.text: Authentic NY slices, courteous and knowledgeable staff. Will definitely be back next time I'm in town!

detailedReviews.author: Jordan Ziman
detailedReviews.text: The pizza and wings are delicious. Pizza size is huge and the wings are large. Cheese bread is kinda disappointing. Other than that delicious. Worth it to make the trip to pick it up.

detailedReviews.author: Beau
detailedReviews.text: I was excited to try this place after seeing it says they're using San Marzano based sauce. I ordered a plain pizza with pepperoni. The crust had a good crunch, not overcooked, but it's overshadowed by toughness. The sauce was sweet, not salty, had good texture, and neutral in flavor.  The cheese lacked prominence, wasn't very cheesy and milky like mozzarella is supposed to be, more akin to a shredded cheese blend. The prices are higher than comparables. If you do a custom pizza becareful if the toppings are the same as one of their other pizzas as it'll be more expensive. Overall the pizza I had was decent but not remarkable. I'd like to try the Queens based on the photo, so I might go back in the future. In my opinion the cheese and crust needs improvement at this price point, especially for the plain that I had.

detailedReviews.author: Lynn Quilan
detailedReviews.text: I'm giving them 5 stars as the pizza is truly NY style and so is the flavor.  The pizza crust was perfect.  The menu is missing White Pizza, and even though it is more of a take out they should have  a restroom.   There is no where to wash hands.

detailedReviews.author: Clarissa Goldsack
detailedReviews.text: We ordered two gyros to be picked up. The meat was hard, way over cooked. The first and the last time we will order from here. AWFUL!!!
